# VIS — Visual Impact Software · environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored) for local development,
# or set the same values in your Cloudflare Pages production
# environment. Vite replaces `import.meta.env.VITE_*` references at
# build time with the static value found here.

# ─── Population-exposure overlay ──────────────────────────────────────
# URL of a Cloud-Optimised GeoTIFF (COG) that the in-browser
# `geotiff.js` lookup will fetch via HTTP Range requests to compute
# "people inside the headline damage radius". The default points at
# WorldPop's 2020 1 km global mosaic, which the browser CANNOT reach
# directly because `data.worldpop.org` does not emit
# `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` headers — the lookup short-circuits
# to "Population data unavailable" on the first failure to keep the
# console clean.
#
# To enable the feature in production, set this to a CORS-enabled
# mirror. Three options in order of cost:
#   1. Cloudflare Worker proxy in front of WorldPop (free up to
#      100 k requests/day; set `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *`).
#   2. R2 / S3 re-host of the same COG (≈ 80 MB) with the CORS
#      header set on the bucket.
#   3. JRC GHSL on AWS Open Data — already CORS-enabled per
#      bucket policy; verify the path you choose.
#
# Leave commented out to keep the population block hidden.
# VITE_POPULATION_COG_URL=https://vis-population.example.workers.dev/ppp_2020_1km_Aggregated.tif

# ─── Plausible analytics (opt-in) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Set to your Plausible domain to enable the DNT-aware analytics
# tracker. Leave empty / unset to disable in dev and production
# alike (the tracker is silent when this is missing).
# VITE_PLAUSIBLE_DOMAIN=
